title: Google\Cloud\PubSub\V1\PubsubMessage
name: PubsubMessage
description:
A message that is published by publishers and consumed by subscribers. The message must contain either a non-empty data field or at least one attribute.

Note that client libraries represent this object differently depending on the language. See the corresponding client library documentation for more information. See Quotas and limits for more information about message limits.

Generated from protobuf message google.pubsub.v1.PubsubMessage

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.data
params.description: The message data field. If this field is empty, the message must contain at least one attribute.

params.name: data.message_id
params.description: ID of this message, assigned by the server when the message is published. Guaranteed to be unique within the topic. This value may be read by a subscriber that receives a PubsubMessage via a Pull call or a push delivery. It must not be populated by the publisher in a Publish call.

params.name: data.publish_time
params.description: The time at which the message was published, populated by the server when it receives the Publish call. It must not be populated by the publisher in a Publish call.

params.name: data.ordering_key
params.description: Identifies related messages for which publish order should be respected. If a Subscription has enable_message_ordering set to true, messages published with the same ordering_key value will be delivered to subscribers in the order in which they are received by the Pub/Sub system. EXPERIMENTAL: This feature is part of a closed alpha release. This API might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.
